=== 1. EXECUTION: ===

To compile the program, on the terminal enter the following commands:

	qmake -project QT+=widgets
	qmake
	make

To run the program, on the terminal enter the following command:

	./a4 [width] [height]

=== 2. PROGRAM USE: ===

To run the program use ./a4 [width] [height]

== 3. ALGORITHMS and DESIGN DECISIONS: ===

All objects drawn are instances of a Shape class, which defines colour, kd, ks values, and an intersect function.
Lights are instances of spheres.
Quads and triangles are first tested to see if they intersect that plane, then if inside the triangle/inside the cube that contains that plane.
Reflection depth set to 7

=== 4. FILES SUBMITTED: ===

algebra.h
algebra.cpp
main.cpp
polyroots.h
polyroots.cpp
readme

=== 5. IMAGES SUBMITTED: ===

Phong illumination model components using gold reflectivity attributes.
diffuse will show shadows.
images/
		ambientGold.png
		diffuseGold.png
		specularGold.png
Regular dual lighting, reflections, no triangle
images/
		noTriangle.png

Different lights on/off
images/
		centerLightOnly.png
		backLeftLightOnly.png
		leftLightOnly.png
		allLights.png


=== 6. PROGRAM ASSUMPTIONS: ===

tested on lab computers on resolutions 800x600 and 2000x2000
